RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 74. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MALIBU ROCK STAR settled just off the pace and off the rail, started a bid leaving the seven sixteenths pole and challenged FANEUIL HALL nearing the three eighths, contested a close disadvantage near the rail on the far turn, took the lead toward the eighth pole and was steadily handled in the lane. The latter stalked the early pace three wide then pulled himself to the front approaching the three eighths pole, contested the edge off the rail most of the far turn, was met toward the head of the lane but stayed on to the finish. MOSES WATER stalked off the rail, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and raced in the three path of the turn, ran evenly to late stretch but flattened toward the wire. MAJOR NELSON saved ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. AWESOME STRIKE dropped well off the early pace in the two and three paths, left the first turn outside and picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, ran in the three path of the far turn and showed little more. AFLEET AIRO came away awkwardly but took over and rated a short lead inside, was met approaching the three eighths pole and gave way past the pole.

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 3/8,rail far turn,little in lane

PYEONG CHANG rated a slim lead inside, was met leaving the first turn and dueled from that point, but dropped back at the rail approaching the quarter pole and had to settle for second. PRINCE OF FENTON rated close four wide on the first turn, challenged into the backstretch but dropped back past the five sixteenths pole and faded in the three path of the far turn. RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEVER COMPROMISE stalked off the rail on the first turn, challenged toward the three eighths pole and took the nod between horses approaching the five sixteenths, contested at a close disadvantage nearest the rail on the turn, recovered the lead past the eighth pole and dug in determinedly to eke out a win over the game challenge of GOLDEN APPEAL, who stalked three wide and challenged toward the three eighths pole, took a slim lead two deep on the far turn, but was met past the eighth pole and ceded; grudgingly. AUBURN MILL raced boxed at the rail into the first turn, started a bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the four path, left the turn outside and finished well while gaining on the top two. REY O REYES took over and moved to the inside to rate the pace, was met and dueled approaching the three eighths pole but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and weakened in the lane. STRINGFELLA rounded the opening turn in the three path, left the turn outside and bid toward the three eighths pole but showed little response.

HAIR OF THE DOG saved ground on the opening turn, was pulled up with a fatal injury leaving the turn and was euthanized on the track.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 7F Dirt CR: 89. Allowance Purse 33900. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 1 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allo wances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: C R'S MANDATE saved ground on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and angled five wide approaching the eighth pole, lugged in while taking the lead under left hand urging mid-stretch and lasted well under steady handling. OVERLY CRITICAL broke outward and into Run To Daylight and raced off the rail on the first turn, started a bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn near the rail, dueled to a slim brief lead mid-stretch but was outfinished from that point. HOT FUDGE SONDE was bumped outward and into Overly Critical leaving the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, angled out into the stretch and finished well outside. JUBA'S NOTION settled in the three path on the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole and raced three wide on the far turn, was forced in and shut off mid-stretch, then nipped from third under the wire. BRISTOL CHANNEL rated a slim lead inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole and dueled at even terms from that point, contested the rail on the far turn, was met and bumped toward mid-stretch and flattened stride. HUMPTY GRUMPTY raced with the pace two deep, challenged from the three eighths pole, contested even terms two deep on the far turn but was pinched back and roughed mid-stretch. RUN TO DAYLIGHT was bumped at the break, rounded the opening turn off the rail, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole and raced close off the rail on the far turn, but weakened in the lane. TARAASHOQ saved ground. STORMIN ROCKET ducked outward and into Hot Fudge Sonde leaving the gate, raced in the three path on the first turn and showed little response. HE ROLLS stalked three wide on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened on the far turn. After posting the inquiry, the Stewards reviewed a claim of foul against the rider of Juba's Notion for interference mid-stretch, lodged by the rider of Humpty Grumpty. Also, a claim of foul was levied against the rider of C R's Mandate for interference mid-stretch, lodged by the rider of Juba's Notion. As a result, C R's Mandate was disqualified to sixth place for causing the chain reaction in mid-stretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Run to Daylight
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,off rail,chased 3/8,off rail far turn,weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 9 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 14500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. EARTHQUAKEDIRECTOR settled two deep on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path and dueled through the stretch for third. MAKE THE WAY CLEAR saved early ground, bid nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the five path of the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. DREAMERS REWARD moved to the inside and rated the pace, came under pressure when challenged by We B Shackin nearing the three eighths pole, was met at the rail approaching the quarter, remained a close factor through the turn but weakened toward mid-stretch. ITS OVER rounded the first turn in the three path, bid nearing the three eighths pole then flattened in the four path of the far turn. MR. MOSLEY rated close to the early pace inside, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole then weakened at the rail on the far turn. DEJOHN raced off the rail on the first turn, gave chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, but faded at the rail on the far turn. UNDER FIRE rated off the pace in the three path on the opening turn, gave chase into the backstretch then weakened off the rail on the far turn.
